This seems very useful for categories: 
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
my_data['Sex'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(my_data['Sex']) 
my_data['BP'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(my_data['BP'])
my_data['Cholesterol'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(my_data['Cholesterol']) 
my_data

This for checking missing values:
my_data.isnull().sum()

Can also map a target variable to numeric values in a different way: 
custom_map = {'drugA':0,'drugB':1,'drugC':2,'drugX':3,'drugY':4}
my_data['Drug_num'] = my_data['Drug'].map(custom_map)
my_data

For corolation: 
my_data.drop('Drug', axis=1).corr()['Drug_num']

For practice:
Age	Sex	BP	Cholesterol	Na_to_K	Drug	Drug_num
0   1   2   3           4               5
For parameter 'Sex' : M -> 1, F -> 0 <br>
For parameter 'BP' : High -> 0, Low -> 1, Normal -> 2<br>
For parameter 'Cholesterol' : High -> 0, Normal -> 1

'drugA':0,'drugB':1,'drugC':2,'drugX':3,'drugY':4